SYMPTOM_TEXT: 41yo male with history of HLD, LBP, and tobacco use who presented to care initially at the with chest pain. He received the second dose of the Moderna vaccine on 18MAR21 at clinic and within 14 hours developed chills and myalgias. He denies any immediate onset of symptoms after receiving the vaccine. The following day he reports experiencing chest pain 24 hours after the vaccine was administered that progressively worsened over the subsequent 36 hours that finally prompted him to seek care. He describes the pain as a central non-radiating squeezing pain that worsened with movement and breathing. He waited to seek care because he reports several of the soldiers in his unit have experienced similar chest pain that eventually resolved.   He reports being at his baseline health prior to receiving the vaccine and denies any fever, cough, rhinorrhea, congestion, malaise, vomiting, diarrhea, or rash.   Upon initial presentation to care at clinic he was noted to have a Tropnon I of 0.9, WBC of 14, elevated CRP (7.3), and temp to 101.4. Patient was given ASA, Plavix, Lovenox, Tylenol, and Ceftriaxone.    Since arriving to clinic and EKG was obtained showing ST elevation in lead 1 and avF concerning for ischemia and underwent a left heart catheterization which was clear of obstruction. Serial high sensitivity Tropnonin levels have been trended to peak of 465. Respiratory viral panel to include SARS COV-2 was negative. Cardiac MRI was consistent with myopericarditis, and show mildly reduced EF for 46%. Blood cultures have not grown any organism. His chest pain has resolved since starting Aspirin and Colchicine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my first does of Moderna on March 23, 2021. I had no reaction in the first 15 minutes.   My husband and I left the site and stopped to do some shopping about 5 miles down the road from the site.  I was driving.  When I got out of the car, I immediately noticed that I was unsteady, I thought I was just being clumsy until I walked around my car to help my husband ( I am his caretaker) out of the car but I was collapsing and needed to steady myself against the car and get my way back to the car because of intense dizziness.  When I got back into the car, I asked him if he could make it to the restaurant and get me some water.  He did and I drank a bottle of water.  At this time I felt like I was going to have the runs and throw up at the same time so I drove through the parking lot and used the bathroom at the restaurant.   I was a little dizzy but it was not as intense as when I first got out of the car.  I was able to walk to the bathroom and back out without any difficulty.  I did have the runs but the feeling of throwing up passed.  We got back into the car and waited until I felt safe to drive.  After another 15 minutes I drove home.  During the drive I felt sick again and had to stop in a parking lot and throw up.  After throwing up, I felt fine and drove the rest of the way home.  I was able to make it into the condo with no problem and take a shower.  I felt steady and no longer sick.  I went to bed for a couple hours and then got up and ate some food which I kept down. During the rest of the day, I took it easy.  Today I feel fine.  No headache.  I will write if I  have any other problems.  I am wondering if anyone else has had a similar experience.?  Should I take the second dose?
OTHER_MEDS: Alendronate Sodium Tablets USP,   Tylenol 8 hr.  Clonazepam, .25 at bedtime.  Centrum - one a day.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt had history of anaphylaxis related to bee stings. We asked if he had ever had a reaction to another vaccine and he said no. Pt came up saying he wasn't feeling well during the observation period, within about 5-10 minutes after receiving the vaccination. He look very pale and clammy. I asked if he was ok and he shook his head. Tried to grab a chair for him and he started to collapse. With some help I was able to get him to the ground without injury. We called 911 and I grabbed an epipen. I tried to assess the patient, and he was unable to tell me if he was having any trouble breathing or if his lips/mouth/tongue was swelling. He was conscious but couldn't speak coherently. I administered the epipen to his right lateral thigh due to his history of anaphylaxis with bee stings. We were able to lay him down while waiting for the ambulance. His color started to return and he was able to respond to questions, but was still slightly confused. He did tell me at this point that he has had similar reactions after vaccines and blood work. The paramedics arrived and took the patients vitals and took him to the hospital.
OTHER_MEDS: None that we are aware of

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within a minute or so of the injection, I started to feel wooozy and like my chest was getting tight. My heart rate felt like it had jumped and my heart was pounding. I started to feel like it was very hot and I was getting somewhat nauseated and feeling like I might pass out. I checked my smart watch and my heart rate had jumped to over 120. The lady who administered the shot got the EMT on site and they took me for observation. They took my blood pressure and it was 157/114 (which is far beyond the norm for me). They took an EKG on site which they said was not alarming in any way. They checked my blood sugar and it was normal. My oxygen level stayed within a normal range. I had some mild feeling of itching/tingling  in my mouth and felt like I had a lump in my throat like a marble. My BP and HR came down some after about 15 minutes but was still high. They called an ambulance and had me go to an ER for further observation since the feeling in my mouth and throat was not resolving and my BP was not coming down to a better range after about 30 minutes. By the time I got to the ER and they monitored me, my BP was still 154/70 and my HR was still in the 80s while at rest. They kept me in observation for long enough for the doctor to feel that I was not in any immediate danger so they discharged me with instructions to return to the ER if things got worse.

progressive shortness of breath; hypoventilation; dysphagia; severe asthenia; mild upper abdominal pain; inability to eat; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable physician. An 83-year-old female patient received the second dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 MRNA VACCINE), via an unspecified route of administration on 14Feb2021 (at the age of 83-years-old) as a single dose for COVID-19 immunization. Medical history included right partial nephrectomy for renal cell carcinoma (RCC) in the remote past, hypertension, obstructive sleep apnea, hypothyroidism, morbid obesity, motion sickness, unspecified allergy as the patient cannot tolerate anything but paracetamol (TYLENOL), acute on chronic respiratory failure secondary to centrilobular emphysema. Ongoing concomitant medications included levothyroxine sodium (LEVOXYL) tablet, meclizine hcl tablet for motion relief and hydrochlorothiazide/ triamterene (DYAZIDE) capsule. The patient previously took paracetamol (TYLENOL). The patient previously received the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 MRNA VACCINE; Lot number: EL3247) on 22Jan2021 (at the age of 83-years-old) in the left arm and experienced difficulty breathing, ground glass opaque lung problem, weak, nausea, "pain on rt.side waist around to back, down to lower belly", slight temp almost 100. On an unspecified date in Feb2021, the patient presented to the hospital with progressive shortness of breath and inability to eat for two days. The patient reportedly received the second dose of BNT162B2 four days prior to coming to the emergency room (ER). In the ER, the patient reported severe asthenia, mild upper abdominal pain and dysphagia, all as of an unspecified date. The patient underwent a CTA in the ER, on Feb2021, which showed no acute pulmonary embolism, or no ground glass infiltrates. The patient was admitted to the hospital on 21Feb2021 at 17:51 for management of worsening shortness of breath. Due to the patient's acute on chronic respiratory failure secondary to centrilobular emphysema and obesity, hypoventilation (as of an unspecified date in Feb2021) was further complicated by obstructive sleep apnea, thus, the patient was admitted to "MedSurg". The patient did not present with COVID-19 or COPD. The BMP was 226 at the time of admission. The patient was started on supplemental oxygen and additionally started on CPAP at night. She was seen by a pulmonologist who recommended Salmeterol Xinaf/ fluticasone (ADVAIR). Pulmonology also recommended to work-up any underlying unaddressed coronary artery disease contributing to the patient's shortness of breath. The patient underwent an echocardiogram on Feb2021 with regadenoson (LEXISCAN) for her shortness of breath which was within normal limits. As the patient additionally reported dysphagia at the time of admission, she was evaluated by a speech and swallow evaluation specialist as well as a gastroenterologist. A GI swallow series was recommended which the patient underwent on Feb2021 and was found to have no active signs of oropharyngeal or esophageal dysphagia. The patient additionally underwent a physical exam on 24Feb2021 at 08:00 with the following results. Vital signs: Temp: 98.2, Pulse: 69, Resp: 17, B/P (MAP): 98/62 (74), Pulse Ox: 96, O2 Delivery: Nasal cannula, O2 flow rate:2.00. HEENT: Pupils equal round reactive light accommodation, no lymphadenopathy noted, neck vens were apple. CVS: S1-S2 normal, no appreciable murmur rub or gallop noted. Respiratory: Good Inspiratory effort, good air entry bilaterally, no rhonchi, Rales or wheezes heard. Gl: Abdomen soft, nontender nondistended, bowel sounds heard, no organomegaly detected. Extremities: Bilateral lower extremities Shaw no edema, bilateral dorsalis pedis 2+, skin appeared intact. Neurological: Patient alert and oriented x3, strength 5x5 in all 4 extremities, no signs of focal neurological deficits. Skin: No clear breakdown or rashes noted. The patient was being discharged home on 24Feb2021 at 08:04 with a CPAP machine. The patient was prescribed Cefuroxime axetil (CEFTIN) 250mg Tablet orally twice a day; Salmeterol Xinaf/ fluticasone (ADVAIR) 250-50 diskus 1 puff twice a day for progressive shortness of breath and hypoventilation. The patient had been advised to follow-up with a pulmonologist for an outpatient pulmonary function test. The clinical outcome of progressive shortness of breath, hypoventilation, inability to eat, dysphagia, severe asthenia and mild upper abdominal pain was unknown. The reporting physician considered that BNT162B2 had no causal effect on the events reported.  Information on the lot/batch number has been requested.; Sender's Comments: In agreement with the HCP reporter, the reported events  do not appear to be related to the subject vaccine. The events likely represent intercurrent medical conditions, possibly associated with the patient's history of  emphysema. This case will be reassessed upon receipt of follow-up information.  The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Patient stated in report was given his second COVID Moderna dose too early, on day 20. Pt had an appointment scheduled for day 30 but presented early and it was not caught by registration or by the medical provider until after the 2nd dose had been given. The patient was informed of this vaccine administration error, and advised per current CDC recommendations he should not receive any more vaccines. The patient was monitored for the recommended 15 minutes after receiving the vaccine, and did not report having any side effects. He was advised to contact the medical provider on site if any problems arose in the future. Information from both vaccine doses is recorded in the company's EMR. SYMPTOM_TEXT: The patient is a 41 yo male with a history of seasonal allergic rhinitis who experienced DVT and PE temporally related to Pfizer BioNTech COVID vaccine dose #2 receipt.  He is a Service Member and reported  high levels of baseline activity, including running 10 miles each Saturday. He received vaccine #1 25 JAN 21 (EN5318) without AE. He received dose #2 on 16 FEB 21, (EN6200). He experienced no immediate symptoms suggestive of IgE event. On day 1 he reports feeling cold, mild fatigue but no other symptoms. On day 2 he was baseline. On day 3 he noted numbness, tightness  and discomfort to his right  calf. On day 4 (Saturday), his usual long run day, he experienced dyspnea and lightheadedness after running 20-30 feet. He states he noted tightness in his calf and instead walked the track while his wife completed her run. He rested day 5.  Day 6 he noted significant edema to his calf, which he describes as double normal in size, and iced it. Day 7, he tried to schedule with PCP and based on triage was sent to ER. ER diagnosed R DVT and bilateral PE's. He was admitted overnight, started anticoagulation therapy. He saw hematology, and the workup was negative for other causes.

Initial symptoms of the first shot included injection site pain, neck soreness, and severe headache that would come and go.    The next day I was so exhausted I couldn't work for 2 days.  I barely got out of bed until about 40 hours after the shot where I was able to get out and do some gardening.   The reason I am filling this out was at right around 72 hours after the vaccine, I was laying down watching a YouTube video feeling quite relaxed.  I then experienced a tachycardia event where my heart rate went up to 120 and stayed there for about an hour.  I remained calm and was not experiencing anxiety, but the heart rate persisted.  I have had this happen before in panic attacks, but it's quite rare and I am in acute, high level stress.    Almost 2 weeks later to the day, I had another tachycardia, stronger than any I've had my entire life that only lasted about 7 seconds, but I would estimate my heart rate jumped to over 250.   I thought I was going to go into cardiac arrest it was so jarring.  I'm not sure if that one was related to the vaccine.

Within 6 to 7 minutes from receiving the 1st dose I experienced the following symptoms: Cool sensation in my chest area and a little bit of pressure and 2 seconds later I experienced a fast heartbeat for 3-5 minutes. The nurses at the center took my blood pressure and it was high along with the fast heartbeat. They continued to take my blood pressure and they kept saying it was high. They also said I had a faint heart beat. The fast heart beat subsided after several minutes, but I felt a calm/relaxing feeling.  The paramedics were called and they took my blood pressure and vitals. They said my heart rate was normal but I did have pre-hypertention blood pressure.  I felt a little strange after the heartbeat subsided like a calm and tired feeling. About an hour and half later I felt sleepy and took a nap for about an hour. When I woke up I still felt calm and a slight pressure in my chest area and my arm was getting sore from the injection site.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: my ears started feeling like they were stopped up and my nose started feeling stuffy.; nose started feeling stuffy; felt flushed; my face was red; what feels like my heart quivering for several seconds followed 3 or 4 times by very slight pain; what feels like my heart quivering for several seconds; This is a spontaneous report received from a contactable consumer (patient). A 72-year-old female patient received BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, lot number: EN6206) at left arm on 08Mar2021 09:30 AM at single dose for COVID-19 immunization. Medical history included gastroesophageal reflux disease, osteoarthritis, nodules on thyroids and allergy to Aspartsme. No covid tested post vaccination. Patient was not pregnant at the time of vaccination. Concomitant medication included pantoprazole sodium sesquihydrate (PANTOPRAZOLE 40). the patient did not receive any other vaccines within 4 weeks prior to the COVID vaccine. Patient previously took Sulfanomide (Sulfa drugs) and had allergy (swelling), codeine and had allergy (nausea). The symptom that has made patient concerned enough to report the possibility of a side effect is: she had her shot this morning and between about 8:55 and 9:15 this evening she had 9 or 10 episodes of what feels like her heart quivering for several seconds followed 3 or 4 times by very slight pain, just below her right breast, she has never experienced such a thing before. (she took baby aspirin around 9:20 in case she was having some kind of heart thing). It's 9:45 pm, and the quivering episodes haven't happened for the last 30 minutes, so maybe they're all cleared up. Earlier, within 30 min of getting the vaccine, her ears started feeling like they were stopped up and her nose started feeling stuffy. Then as she was driving home she felt flushed and looked in the mirror and her face was red, she took one Sudafed in case it was allergies, and those symptoms improved quite a lot. Adverse event start date was 08Mar2021 10:00 AM. Since the vaccination, the patient has not been tested for COVID-19. Unknown if treatment received for ears started feeling like they were stopped up and nose started feeling stuffy. Outcome of what feels like my heart quivering for several seconds followed 3 or 4 times by very slight pain was recovered. Outcome of felt flushed and face was red was recovering and outcome of other events was unknown.   Information on Lot/Batch number was available. Additional information has been requested.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: blood pressure went from normal to 190; feeling her chest tight; couldn't breathe; black spot in her eyes; just a tightness in her throat; sugar is very high; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable nurse (patient). An 80-year-old female patient received bnt162b2 (BNT162B2, Solution for injection), via an unspecified route of administration on 02Mar2021 (Batch/Lot Number: EN9809; Expiration Date: 30Jun2021) as a single dose for COVID-19 immunization. Medical history included diabetic, asthma, allergy, sugar, and thyroid (disorder). The patient also stated that she has a lot of allergies. She was allergic to bees and allergic to bunch of things and many more things. She had her thyroid removed. Concomitant medications included levothyroxine (LEVOTHYROXINE, 100 ug) taken for thyroid (disorder), start and stop date were not reported; metformin (METFORMIN, 100 mg) taken for her sugar, start and stop date were not reported; hydrochlorothiazide (HYDROCHLOROTHIAZIDE, 12.5 pill), taken as diuretic, start and stop date were not reported. The patient reported that she had a very bad reaction from the vaccine, which was 20 minutes her blood pressure went from normal to 190 and she started feeling her chest tight and couldn't breathe (all on 02Mar2021). She also had a black spot in her eyes (02Mar2021). The patient reported that the events started the minute after she got the shot. She was sent to the hospital on 02Mar2021. When she was in the hospital, her blood pressure went up to 244, it is the highest. Her chest was going to have an asthma attack but she didn't develop an asthma attack it was just a tightness in her throat (02Mar2021). She was a day and half in the hospital, trying to get her blood pressure down which went down somehow that she still have over 200 blood pressure. When paraphrased the above concern she stated, "Yeah absolutely want to know what kind of result or what kind of the side effect you are going to have." The patient also stated at the time of report, "I still have my blood pressure is still 200 and my sugar is very high too (unspecified date in Mar2021), is that part of the after effect of the vaccine because I didn't have that before." The patient was hospitalized from 02Mar2021 to 04Mar2021. Therapeutic measures were taken as a result of blood pressure went from normal to 190 (hypertension) and couldn't breathe. The patient stated her doctor put her in the double medicine for the blood pressure. When probed for if patient was still experiencing issue, she stated "No, as soon as I came home I took Benadryl". The patient reported that her breathing improved as soon as she took Benadryl and her chest is probably clear now. As treatment, they gave her blood pressure pills. They gave her Pravastatin 20 mg. Outcome of the event blood pressure went from normal to 190 and sugar is very high was not recovered. Outcome of couldn't breathe was recovering. Outcome of the other events was unknown.; Sender's Comments: Based on the available information, the known safety profile and the temporal association of BNT162B2 administration to the events, a possible contribution of the drug to the events cannot be excluded.  The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committees, and Investigators, as appropriate and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committees, and Investigators, as appropriate.

Vertigo/ severe refractory vertigo; epidemic vertigo; Vomiting; Headache; nausea; Legs locked up and she was temporarly unable to walk; gait instability; Fatigue; paralysis; balance issues; serious neurological problems; post herpetic neuralgia; sores in mouth; rash; temperature of 103; This spontaneous report was received from a 62-year-old female, referring to herself. The patient's pertinent medical history was not reported. Her previous drug reactions or allergies included codeine. Concomitant therapy included atorvastatin calcium (LIPITOR) and candesartan cilexetil (ATACAND) and few other medications. On 20-AUG-2007, the patient was vaccinated with a single dose of zoster Vaccine Live (ZOSTAVAX) (strength, dose, route of administration, anatomical location, lot number, and expiration date were not reported). On 22-AUG-2007, the patient experienced headaches, vertigo, dizziness, nausea and vomiting. In addition her legs locked up on her and she was temporarily unable to walk. When this occurred she had to be hospitalized for one week. While in the hospital many tests were performed (results not reported). Her legs returned to normal but the other adverse symptoms lasted through December 2007, before going away. Subsequently, the patient recovered from headache, vertigo, dizziness, nausea and vomiting. The causality assessment between zoster Vaccine Live (ZOSTAVAX) and the aforementioned events were not reported.    Follow-up (F/U) information was received from the consumer on 05-SEP-2008. On 16-AUG-2007 (previous reported 20-AUG-2007), the patient was vaccinated with a single dose of zoster Vaccine Live (ZOSTAVAX). On 24-AUG-2007, the patient's husband called an ambulance to take her to the emergency room and the patient was admitted to the hospital. The patient told them, she was given the zoster vaccine live (Oka/Merck) vaccination and the patient thought that was what was wrong as that was the only thing different that the patient had experienced and that the patient had been ill since being given the vaccination. The physicians ruled out everything else that would cause her to have these same symptoms. Finally it was concluded that the vaccination was the cause of her symptoms as the patient had not had anything like this before and the patient had not had anything like this since. The patient had go for therapy to learn to walk again properly. The patient took zoster Vaccine Live (ZOSTAVAX) because a lady in her school class had shingles and the virus went to her brain and paralyzed her. The patient recovered.  This is one of two reports received from the same reporter.   F/U had been received on 24-OCT-2008. Concerning a 61-year-old retired female with anxiety disorder, asthma, depression, hyperlipidemia, hypertension, overweight, non-smoker, abstains from alcohol, statin intolerance, hypercholesterolemia and a history of vertigo and migraines in the distant past, abnormal hepatic function, and a family history of heart disease. Additional concomitant therapy included meclizine, montelukast sodium (SINGULAIR), lansoprazole (PREVACID), escitalopram oxalate (LEXAPRO), lorazepam, and albuterol (manufacturer unknown). It was reported that on 24-AUG-2007, the patient was admitted through the emergency room for a work-up and evaluation of severe, refractory vertigo. The patient had been having trouble for about two days prior to admission with lightheadedness, headache, room spinning, and progressive difficulty with ambulation. It was reported that the patient had several near falls. On admission, the patient was unable to walk without  lots of help from her family and she was complaining of severe room spinning and dizziness. She had a CT of the head in the emergency room, which showed no acute abnormalities; however, she was clearly struggling, and she was admitted for a further inpatient work-up and management of her problems. The patient was put on meclizine hydrochloride (ANTIVERT) and intravenous methylprednisolone sodium succinate (SOLU-MEDROL). The physician felt like she had peripheral vestibulopathy. On 26-AUG-2007, an MRI with MRA was performed and the results were normal except for hypoplastic vertebral arteries and proximal basilar artery, which were deemed unlikely to be clinically significant. It was reported that metabolic studies including thyroid studies, cortisol levels, B12, folage, ANA, Lyme titer, HIV, and perioneoplastic studies were performed, all of which were negative. The patient had a slow but favorable response to the events. She was able to walk with less help, and her dizziness was  improved overall. She still had some weakness, but felt better overall. The patient was discharged from the hospital on 28-AUG-2007 with follow-up to be scheduled on an outpatient basis. The physician reported that on 13-SEP-2007, the patient came to the office for a follow up visit. She had a sensation of movement, but otherwise felt diffusely weak since the day before coming to the emergency room and getting prednisone. She was reported to be gradually tapering off the prednisone and was continuing the meclizine hydrochloride (ANTIVERT). On 13-SEP-2007, Lyme titer and HSV titers were performed, the results were all negative. The patient was started on lamotrigine (LAMICTAL) for dizziness, and referred to a physical therapist for vestibular rehab. The physician reported that on 25-SEP-2007, the patient came to the office for a follow up visit. She continued to have difficulties with vertigo as well as associated headache and nausea. The physician referred her to the vestibular  clinic, but had not gone because she reported that "her equilibrium and depth perception were off." The physician recommended that she try the vestibular clinic and a transderm scopolamine patch. The patient reported that she had taken ibuprofen (MOTRIN) for her headache, but it had not helped much. On 25-SEP-20007, the patient called to reported that she had started lamotrigine (LAMICTAL), and was having vertigo, dizziness, sores in mouth and a temperature of 103. The physician recommended that she stop taking lamotrigine (LAMICTAL)and also see her primary care physician, but did not think that the temperature was related to the lamotrigine (LAMICTAL). On 26-SEP-2007, the patient left a message saying that she stopped the lamotrigine (LAMICTAL) but had developed a rash. The physician reported that on 04-OCT-2007, the patient came to the office again for a follow up visit and had dizziness that appeared to be peripheral vestibulopathy. Lab studies were all negative. The patient was  referred to an ENT. The physician reported that on 20-NOV-2007, the patient came to the office again for a follow up visit and reported that she been doing better since her vestibular therapy. She had an ENT consult and the physician did not feel that she had Meniere's disease. The physician reported that on 29-NOV-2007, the patient came to the office again for a follow up visit. Her dizziness had improved, and she had gone to the vestibular clinic, which had helped. She had been doing head positioning exercises at home which have helped. The physician reported that on 30-JUL-2008, the patient came to the office for a follow up visit and reported that her dizziness had gotten better and she had no further symptoms.  It was reported that the patient has a family history of heart attack, her sister died at a relatively young age.  F/U information was received from a lawyer regarding a case in litigation on 26-OCT-2020. On or about 2007, the patient was vaccinated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) for the long-term prevention of shingles and zoster-related conditions (strength, route of administration, anatomical location, lot number, and expiration date were not reported). On an unknown date, reported as subsequent to the vaccination, the patient was treated for postherpetic neuralgia, serious neurological problems, balance issues, paralysis, severe refractory vertigo and headaches. The reporter considered postherpetic neuralgia, nervous system disorder, balance disorder, paralysis, vertigo and headache to be related to zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX).  Upon internal review, diplegia and paralysis were determined to be medically significant events.  records will be provided upon request; Sender's Comments:  US-009507513-0809USA01819:

left arm stiffness, back stiffness, neck stiffness; decreased mobility in all four of his extremities; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of stiff neck in a 68-year-old male patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) (batch number 4Z43X, expiry date unknown) for prophylaxis.   Co-suspect products included PNEUMOCOCCAL 13 VALENT CONJUGATE VACCINE (PREVNAR 13) (batch number DJ7721, expiry date unknown) for prophylaxis.   Previously administered products included Shingrix with an associated reaction of musculoskeletal stiffness (1st dose received on 16th September 2020, refer case US2021062762).   On 28th November 2020, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix and PREVNAR 13. On 5th December 2020, less than a day after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced stiff neck and mobility decreased. Rechallenge with Shingrix was positive. On 1st March 2021, the outcome of the stiff neck and mobility decreased were recovered/resolved. pain all over / bad pain; This case was reported by a consumer via other manufacturer and described the occurrence of general body pain in a 59-year-old male patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingles vaccine) for prophylaxis.   Previously administered products included Chicken pox. Concurrent medical conditions included pain, blood cholesterol increased and testosterone decreased. Concomitant products included hydrocodone, oxycodone, atorvastatin, clomifene citrate (Clomiphene) and ascorbic acid (Vitamin C).   In January 2020, the patient received Shingles vaccine. On an unknown date, less than 2 years after receiving Shingles vaccine and an unknown time after starting atorvastatin, the patient experienced general body pain. On an unknown date, the outcome of the general body pain was recovered/resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the general body pain to be related to Shingles vaccine.  Additional details were provided as follows: The case was reported by patient himself. The patient weight reported in the range of 215 to 220 pounds. The patient received Vitamin D, Vitamin C and eye medications as conmeds. The patient received shingles vaccine in right arm and for 1 and half day to 2 days she experienced all over body pain and this pain was resolved after 2 days. On 6th March 2021, the patient received first dose of Covid- 19 vaccine of Pfizer in left arm and on same day he experienced a bit of itching, just a little bit that made him not comfortable with it for 20 minutes, felt like he was chewing his lips, and his ribs moving quicker. The reporter stated that he was taking pain medications because of him being tortured previously. He told that he took hydrocodone and oxycotton and these medications kept his body stable and he was able to sleep and relax. After 1 day after receiving Covid 19 vaccine, the patient experienced pain in muscles, joints and bones and it was getting worse. The reporter stated that normally his pain was getting better with his medication but on that day his body was not stable, he had pain all over him and he did not have any energy to move. He still had pain and his body was so weak for about 4 to 5 hours. The reporter stated that he was able to do his work all day but now after about 3 to 4 hours on his feet and he gets so tired that he needs to sit. The reporter stated that none of the other people who received Covid vaccine experienced this events. The reporter needs to visit physician every month. The reporter stated that in morning when he woke up he had pain in his joints and his bones, he did not like to use too much medication but this Covid vaccine made him need to use more medication and then caused him to had a headache. Sometimes he drinks a lots of cranberry juice to try to take vaccine out of his system, but it was frustrating because he had not ever been like this, when he had pain like this it reminds him of his torturing and he worried that what has happened to him. The reporter stated that this Covid vaccine was not safe as he believes because it had been almost 10 days and it was not helping him. Note : The conmed Oxycotton was not available in database hence was coded as ocxycodone.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: blood in stools; Cough; Body ache; Chills; Fever; tired; Dizziness; A spontaneous report was received by medical information from a nurse concerning a 63 year old, male patient who developed/experienced: cough (cough), body ache (myalgia), fever (pyrexia), chills (chills), dizziness( dizziness), fatigue (fatigue), tired (tiredness) and blood in stools (haematochezia).   The patient's medical history was not provided other than concomitant medications.  Products known to have been used by the patient, within two weeks prior to the events, included: Metformin, Zinc and B12.    The patient received their presumed first dose of the mRNA-1273 vaccine on 27Jan2021 (Batch #: 032L20A) as it was indicated by the reporter that the patient was due for the next dose around the time of the report. The events occurred following the first dose of the vaccine but exact dates of the events were not provided, only duration in days.   The day following the administration of the vaccine, the patient reported cough, body ache, fever, chills, fatigue and feeling tired. These symptoms lasted for 10 days.   Approximately 2 weeks following the administration of the vaccine, the patient reported dizziness which lasted for 5 days.   The patient took Tylenol for treatment and was noted to be feeling better as of 13Feb2021. No further outcome information was provided.   The patient reported having blood in stools and was seen by their doctor, date of onset was not provided. The doctor indicated this was "probably hemmoroids" and that "he (the patient) was fine and drink lots of liquids." No other treatment or outcome information was provided.    It is unknown if the subject received the second dose of mRNA-1273.    No assessment of causality was provided by the reporting nurse or the patient's doctor.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Fainted in shower; while having dinner fainted, dizziness, and light headed; Body ache; Extreme high fever; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer, concerning a male patient of unspecified age, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine and experienced fever, body ache, fainting, dizziness and lightheadedness.  The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter.  On an unknown date, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot number unknown) via unknown route for COVID-19 infection prophylaxis.   On 24-FEB-2021, prior to the onset of events, the patient received their second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot number unknown) intramuscularly on left upper arm for COVID-19 infection prophylaxis.  On 24-FEB-2021, after second dose of vaccine, the patient experienced extreme high fever and body ache. Treatment medication included Tylenol for the event extreme high fever. On 26-FEB 2021, patient was feeling better and was able to walk for an hour. At night, he went to the restaurant for dinner and while having dinner, patient fainted, experienced dizziness and felt light headed. He had ongoing symptoms of dizziness while standing and sitting.  The patient received both scheduled doses of mRNA-1273 prior to the events; therefore, action taken with the drug in response to the events is not applicable.  The outcome of the event, fainting was unknown at the time of this report. The outcome of the events extreme high fever and body ache was resolved on 26-Feb-2021. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Fluid on the ear; Bells palsy; Jaw pain; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer who was a 71-years-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and who experienced: Bells palsy(facial paralysis), jaw pain (pain in jaw), and fluid on ear (middle ear effusion).  The patient did not provide any relevant or specific medical history. Concomitant product use was not provided/unknown by the reporter   On 11 Feb 2021, the patient received her first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number 013M20A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 28 Feb 2021, the patient started to experience jawpain and went to see her doctor. The date of the doctor visit was not provided/unknown by the reporter. The patient was told by the doctor, "she had fluid on ear." Patient endorses, "she has had fluid on ear before and never had that type of pain."  Patient reports she returned for medical care on 06 Mar 2021 and was seen by a nurse practioner. The nurse practioner said she had Bells palsy. Patient indicated "she had all signs on(of) Bells palsy." The patient expressed concern regarding her eyesight as nurse practioner said "she could get dust in eye because of inability to close eye." Patient also wanted a call back on whether or not to take the second dose.   Treatment for the events included: "pregnisone" (presumed to be prednisone, reported as pregnisone 500mg/1000mg) and an anti-viral (reported as valacyclovir 1000mg) which was prescribed by the nurse practioner.   Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported.   Outcome of the events of Bells palsy, jaw pain and fluid on ear was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the onset date of the reported events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Fell after urinating and hit her head; Semi delirious and confused; Cramps were intermittent for 1-2 hours; Tremulous; Low blood pressure; Dizzy; Cold, clammy; Very sweaty; Severe diarrhea; Lost consciousness; Borderline in shock or in shock; Head injury; abdominal discomfort; A spontaneous report was received from a physician concerning a 63-year-old, female patient who developed severe diarrhea, abdominal discomfort, lost consciousness, fell after urinating and hit her head, cold and clammy, very sweaty, low blood pressure, semi delirious, confused, tremulous, cramps, in shock and dizzy.    The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter.     On 03 Mar 2021, approximately four days prior to the onset of the symptoms, the patient received her first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: 041L20A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 06 Mar 2021, the patient experienced severe diarrhoea and abdominal discomfort. At 4 AM she had lost consciousness and fell after urinating and hit her head on the curb of the shower. Her husband found her and when he saw her, she was cold, clammy and very sweaty. Her husband reported that the patient had low blood pressure that caused syncope and caused her to fall. The patient was in a semi-delirious state and was confused, tremulous. The cramps were intermittent for 1-2 hours. The patient was in a borderline shock or in shock as she was very dizzy when she stood up. The events were resolved after four hours. On the next day her temperature was at 98.8 degrees Fahrenheit.   Treatment information was not provided.    Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not provided.  The outcome of the events, diarrhea, abdominal discomfort, loss of consciousness, fall, cold sweats, hyperhidrosis, hypotension, syncope, confusional state, tremors, muscle spasms, shock and dizziness were recovered.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Feeling sleepy yesterday; Itching around the neck and arm  but no rash; Chills; Headache; Nausea; Fever; Body ache; Felt tired; Vomiting; Tired muscle; Passed out in kitchen; Heavy chest which did not affect her breathing but it felt like adrenalin rush; A spontaneous report was received from a 51 year-old female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced chills, headache, nausea (nausea), vomiting (vomiting), fever (pyrexia), itching around the neck and arm but no rash (pruritus), body ache (pain) with tired muscle (muscle fatigue), felt tired (fatigue), passed out in the kitchen (loss of consciousness), heavy chest which did not affect the breathing but it felt like adrenalin rush (chest discomfort) and felt sleepy (somnolence).  The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.   On 06 Mar 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch Number: 012A21A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 06 Mar 2021, 5 to 6 hours after the vaccination, the patient experienced chills, headache, nausea and vomiting, fever, itching around the neck and arm but no rash, body ache, felt tired and passed out in the kitchen. The patient also had heavy chest which did not affect the breathing, but it felt like adrenalin rush. On 07 Mar 2021, the patient felt sleepy and had muscle tiredness. The outcomes of the events, chills, headache, nausea and vomiting, fever, itching around the neck and arm but no rash, body ache with tired muscle felt tired and passed out in the kitchen, heavy chest which did not affect the breathing but it felt like adrenalin rush and felt sleepy, were unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

On 03-MAR-2021, approximately 12 hours prior to onset of first event, the patient received their first planned dose of mRNA-1273 (Lot/Batch number: 022M28A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   Within the first 12 hours of being vaccinated, the patient experienced minor arm soreness, which ended the same day. The next day, she experienced fatigue, headache, shaking and shivering, muscle aches, was getting weak, threwup once, fever, and didn't know who she was. She lived alone and was hollering for someone to help her. She couldn't get out of bed. She was hallucinating; she thought the floor was wet. Her arm was severely swollen and painful.  The patient couldn't lift her arm.  Treatments of these events were not provided.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event is unknown.  The outcome for the events, hallucinations, confusional state, muscular weakness, asthenia, peripheral swelling, pain, fever, headache, fatigue, vomiting, shaking/shivering and muscle aches, were unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, confusional state, muscular weakness, asthenia, peripheral swelling, pain, fever, headache, fatigue, vomiting, shaking/shivering and muscle aches, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. On 11 Mar 2021, approximately within one hour prior to the onset of events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: Unknown) intramuscularly in the right arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. The patient's carbon level was high, needed a pit line and under bypap. The patient also had developed fever. Treatment medications included unspecified antibiotics and bilevel positive airway pressure (BiPAP) given to the patient at the hospital.  Action taken with second dose of mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown. I noticed when I urinated about 09:15 am on 17th, the toilet paper looked pink after I wiped myself. I went again an hour later and I was experiencing irritation and issue with not urinating. This time there was a trickle of blood down the toilet. This is very unusual for me -  have not experienced it before. The pink color on the toilet paper continued for about 4 hours. I was having to go to the bathroom frequently. I upped my fluid intake knowing that it may be a bladder infection. I made an appt with doctor - on the 17th -  by the time I got to see her in the afternoon I saw a physician in the same office as my normal doctor - I saw Dr. - the pink on the toilet paper wasn't happening anymore. Was prescribed Cephalexin -500 mg - twice a day for 5 days. It took until yesterday before I didn't have urgency and irritation and an issue with urinating - at this point - it feels like it may be almost back to normal. We are watching now to make sure if I have any more blood or pink staining, I will get an appt with an urologist.
LAB_DATA: 17th - at my doctor's office - Urine Specimen - Was still blood in the urine and there was also extra white cells They also did a culture with the urine: on Friday afternoon or Saturday - I got a call and they said there was no bladder infection - nothing grew. They said I could keep taking the antibiotic or not. I decided to finish the course.
OTHER_MEDS: Levo-synthroid 100; Albuterol sulfate; Singulair; Metrogel; Prevadent 500+ dental toothpaste; Chlorhexadine gluconate - mouthwash; Allegra; Take occasionally: (as needed depending on season - were not taking them at time of vaccine)  ibupro

I woke up again around 6am with the same severe headache and excruciating  pain in my left arm at the injection site and tried to get up to get some ibuprofen. Client received 1st Pfizer Covid Vaccine (Lot # ER8732, Exp 3/24/21) approximately 1545. Client was sitting in post vaccine waiting area when she alerted EMT she was feeling lightheaded and dizzy. RN  joined and began to assess client. Vitals at 1600: blood pressure 126/80 pulse 84, respirations 18. Alert and oriented. No swelling noted. Client denied shortness of breath. Per client no history of allergies or reaction to vaccines in the past. Client asked for water. PHN  joined team, client instructed to take small sips of water. Concomitant medications reported were amoxicillin, gliclazide, acetylsalicylic acid, amlodipin, atorvastatin, clonazepam, hydroxyzine, multi vitamin, inhaler, albuterol as needed and nebulizer, all were used for an unknown indication. On 05 Mar 2021, the patient had allergic reaction at the vaccine site, felt sick to their stomach, dizzy, heart racing immediately after inoculation with the vaccine. Pharmacist thought they were having a panic attack, but patient says no. That evening developed a fever. On 06 Mar 2021, the patient felt suffocation in chest that was tolerable. On 07 Mar 2021, the patient experienced bad suffocation in chest, super dizzy and passed out in chair. Stated that they were knocked out for 35 minutes. Suffocation decreased. Treatment details included none.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The outcome of events, super dizzy, moderate chest pains, fever and right hand feels tingly with numbness was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events (suffocation feeling, abdominal discomfort, pyrexia, tachycardia, and vaccination site reaction) a causal relationship cannot be excluded. I didn't know what was happening to me.  I remained calm.  I drove to my house to seek help from my husband.  At 1:10-1:15 p.m., I took sips of water and tried to eat something.  I started to feel better.  At 1:30 PM, the swelling, etc. ... gone.  From that point, no further swelling reaction other than the start of the effects.

All read to me the CDC guidelines.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1st vaccine taken at 6 pm on Sunday.  Monday did fine first half of the day. About 12:30 pm, was cleaning a crib at work, had trouble getting up from a squatting position to standing position.  By 3:30 pm, felt horrible - hurt particularly in hip joints, knee joints, also in ankles, and wrists.  Called in to work - took PTO on Tuesday, could not move hips and knees without some assist (on her own), felt like her hips and knees "had rusted."  Felt she had done something very foolish by taking the shot.  Had some severe mental anguish for about 24 hours wondering if this would progress to something more serious (says she was concerned about something like Guillain-Barre Syndrome). Suffered through the night.  Had fever (did not check temperature) and chills.  Was able to get up on Wednesday and it was better.  By 10 am on Wednesday, it was gone.  Had pain, but not swelling at the injection site.  Had to take 2 days PTO days.    2nd vaccine given at about 1:30 pm on a Sunday.  By Sunday evening, chills off and on, fatigue.  Sunday night, when she would sit or lay down, she would feel like she was moving - almost like she was on a boat or had been on a boat, and had a nauseating headache from back of neck and up into her head.  Had alternations of feeling warm and chills. By Tuesday, felt better by 3 pm.  Still feel a little woozy this morning.  Feels like a gentle movement inside like she has been on a boat.  Makes her a little nauseated.  Denies any pain now.  Had pain, but not swelling at the injection site.  Had to take two PTO days..

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Death; unconscious; in and out of consciousness; weak, very weak; blood pressure was very low; little light headed; A spontaneous report was received from consumer concerning a 88 years old female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced a little light headed/ dizziness, weak, very weak/asthenia, blood pressure was very low/ hypotension, in and out of consciousness/depressed level of consciousness, unconscious/ loss of consciousness and passed away.  The patient's medical history was reported as heart issues. Concomitant medications taken by the patient included levothyroxine, isosorbide, acetylsalicylic acid, metoprolol, furosemide, warfarin, antibiotics.   On 3 Mar 2021, prior to the onset of the event, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 015M20A) intramuscularly in the right arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 3 Mar 2021, when the patient got home the night, after getting the shot, patient was a little lightheaded, she seemed to be okay on 04 Mar 2021 and 05 Mar 2021. Patient had complained of being weak and her blood pressure was very low on 08 Mar 2021. She was progressively started getting weaker. On 09 Mar 2021, she was very weak and was in and out of consciousness. Patient was taken to the hospital, and she became unconscious and  then passed away. Patient passed away on 09 Mar 2021.  The patient died on 09 Mar 2021. The cause of death was unknown.  Plans for an autopsy were unknown.   Treatment activities for event was not provided.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not applicable.   The outcome of events,  unconscious, a little light headed, weak, very weak,  blood pressure was very low, in and out of consciousness was unknown. The outcome was considered fatal.; Reporter's Comments: This is a case of sudden death in a 88-year-old female patient with a history of heart issues, who died 6 days after receiving first dose of vaccine. Very limited information has been provided at this time.; Reported Cause(s) of Death: Unknown cause of death

SYMPTOM_TEXT: In observation the patient began to experience urticaria, and had a history of anaphylaxis.  He complained of an itchy forehead, which we began to monitor.  He then felt thickness of the base of the tongue, tingling of the lips.  He was given an oral dose of 25mg of Bendryl.  We began to monitor his pulse ox levels.  He remained at 98-99 sat on room air.  His heart rate ranged from 60-68.  He then experienced more itching of the arms, and continued itching of the forehead, thickness of the tongue.  A second oral dose of 25mg Benedryl was given.  After continual monitoring for 45 minutes his symptoms began to subside.  After another 15 minutes he felt his symptoms had resolved.  His final pulse/ox reading was 99% with a pulse of 67.  He was instructed to follow up with his PCP.  He was also instructed to monitor himself for further symptoms.  ER protocols given.  He left on his own.
ALLERGIES: insect bites, vaccinations, Previous anahylaxis allergies

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Graves disease; shortness of breath; tachycardia; A spontaneous report was received from a health professional concerning a 49-years-old female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and had graves disease (basedow's disease), shortness of breath (dyspnoea), tachycardia  No medical history was provided. No concomitant medications were provided.  On 12 Feb 2021, the patient received the second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: not provided), intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 12 Feb 2021, the patient developed tachycardia and shortness of breath. On 13 Feb 2021, she had medical evaluation done that showed she did not have a pulmonary embolus. On 23 Feb 2021, lab data showed undetectable thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH). On 01 Mar 2021, she had full set of thyroid function tests that still showed an undetectable TSH and elevated free T4 and a total T3. She was confirmed to have Graves' disease (medically significant) based off elevated thyroid stimulating immunoglobulins.  The patient had been started on treatment.  The patient received both scheduled doses of mRNA-1273 prior to the event, therefore action taken with the drug in response to the event is not applicable.   The outcome of the events of graves disease (basedow's disease), shortness of breath (dyspnea), tachycardia was unknown.  The reporter assessed the events to be possibly related to the study drug.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Patient presented at vaccination table after having documents and appointment reviewed by non-clinical staff, and identity was confirmed by nurse vaccinator using two unique identifiers (including DOB). Nurse vaccinator reviewed patient's responses to screening form completed in PrepMod and screened patient to confirm she was feeling well, had no history of anaphylaxis, does not carry an epi-pen for allergies, and had not received COVID vaccine previously. RN vaccinator educated patient on possible side effects of Moderna product. Patient indicated she wished to be immunized, received Moderna vaccine, and proceeded to observation area where she waited for fifteen minutes before departing from clinic without reporting any adverse event. Patient was later found to be five months under the minimum age of 18 years for receiving Moderna COVID-19 vaccine, thereby rendering the medication as administered outside the age limit of the applicable order.   Immediate Action/Intervention: Patient was under observation for CDC-mandated 15-minute period following vaccine administration. Upon review of records and discovery that dose was administered to patient who was five months too young to be eligible. Director of Nursing was informed of error and tasked with completing required documentation and performed root cause analysis.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received first dose of Pfizer vaccine 3/24/21. Patient became unsteady and was directed to stretcher. Patient has a hx of HTN and reports not taking his BP medication for "a while." Patient was unsure what BP medication he was on. Reports potentially taking Lasix and Vit K. Patient reports not eating or drinking prior to receiving the vaccination. Alert and oriented. Denies SOB/chest pain.     Vitals taken at 10:45AM:  BP 197/11  HR 75 SPO2 98% RA   ED rapid response called. Pt unable to stand up from stretcher.   Patient was taken to ED and neurology was consulted.  Neurology noted:  55-year-old man past medical history of hypertension coming with uncontrolled hypertension systolic over 220.  Concern for gait instability, no evidence of strength weakness on any extremity with confrontational testing.  No evidence of change in altered mental status, no evidence of cranial nerve palsy, and no evidence of sensory loss.   No evidence of coordination problems with finger-to-nose testing and heel-to-shin testing bilaterally.  He exhibits 5 out of 5 confrontational testing to all extremities muscles as above albeit with giveaway weakness.  NIHSS 0.     Although patient presents within TPA window he has had no disabling symptoms and therefore is not a candidate for TPA.  Although the patient presents with a mechanical thrombectomy window he has no disabling symptoms and no evidence of LVO either on exam or my preliminary read of his CTA head and neck.  As such he is not a candidate for mechanical thrombectomy.   Symptoms do not localize well although patient presents with clear hypertensive urgency versus hypertensive emergency.  Would recommend full medical work-up for this condition as we rule out signs of acute ischemic stroke.   Patient passes dysphagia screen in the ED.  Recommendation: 1. Admit to Observation.  2. MRI brain without contrast 3. Obtain stroke labs A1c, TSH, lipid profile 4. PT OT consult evaluation and treat 5. Social worker and case management consult for stroke work-up

I believe the shot was improperly administered too close to my shoulder joint, and as a result, I have experienced increasing pain over the last 11 days.  Initially, there was mild pain (I would rate a 3-4 out of 10) near the injection site immediately which persisted for days as expected after getting a shot; mainly discomfort during sleep and when moving my arm. Pain has become progressively worse, and not better as reported to be a normal and expected side effect. At day 10 I called my PCP to go in for an exam. She ordered an Xray and prescribed muscle relaxers. Xray showed no signs of breakage (as expected).  Today is day 11 and  I can barely move or lift my arm without severe discomfort, I would rate the pain as severe (9 out of 10) when moving or lifting my arm, rotating shoulder, sleeping on it.  While I have not been diagnosed with anything in particular yet, I believe I have a shoulder injury relating to improper vaccine administration (SIRVA). I have requested to be referred to a shoulder specialist for evaluation. I have not had prior injuries or symptoms in this area. I am an active and healthy person with no known health conditions and this is very troubling. I am a strong advocate for COVID vaccines, yet, I must say this experience has me questioning my decision to get one.  I never knew this could happen, and I sincerely hope my shoulder is not permanently impacted by this event.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt. arrived just prior to the clinic at 4:00pm  for her scheduled vaccination.  While there she informed the educator and the vaccinator that she had unknown environmental allergies and indicated that she had a history of anaphylaxis.  She and the nurse reviewed the ingredients in the fact sheet and the patient stated that she was not aware/did not have any allergies to the ingredients to the Moderna vaccine.  She stated that she had had other vaccinations Flu and pneumonia with no issues.  After discussing with the nurse, she decided to proceed with getting the vaccine.  0.5 ML of Moderna vaccine was administered to her right Deltoid at approximately 4:00 pm.  She was informed that she would need to stay and be evaluated for 30 due to her history of anaphylaxis.  At 4:17 patient reported to the monitors that she was starting to feel like her throat was tightening and that she was having difficulty breathing.  At 4:19 pm she began pulling out her epinephrine to draw it up.  RN took over for her as she was struggling and administer 0.5 mg SQ to her right lower abdomen. BP was 180/80 at 4:19 pm.  911 was called.  Pt. continued to have difficulty breathing  and talking.  At 4:27 pm 50mg Benadryl IM was administered to her right deltoid.  She was still having difficulty breathing and her respirations were rapid.  At 4:28 pm  Epinephrine 0.5mg SQ was administered to her lower left abdomen.  BP at 4:28 pm was 150/100, Pulse was 154.  At approximately 4:33 pt. reported some relief, her respirations were not noted to be as rapid but she reported continued difficulty breathing.  At approximately 4:35 EMS was on scene.  EMS intubated patient in the EMS and transported to Hospital.  Pt. is in critical condition in the ICU.  This RN called to check on patient on 03/24/2021 and it was reported by her nurse that she coded multiple times through the night and was made a DNR and will be placed on comfort care and it was anticipated she may pass in the next day or two.
LAB_DATA: Pt was intubated and transferred to the hospital.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I have Moderna arm (starting about 8am on 3/22/2021), and a pinprick sensation on right forearm starting evening of 3/22/2021. It progressed to itchiness in V1 distribution of right-sided scalp. As of 3/24/2021 there is pruritis of V1 distribution of right scalp down to the eye. There is some mild redness to right eye and skin surrounding eye and forehead. Mild enough that I cannot decide if it is from rubbing and scratching it versus being present at baseline. It is helped by a concoction similar to Icy Hot (not applied near eye). I have had chickenpox as a child. There are no vesicles (so far). I am not immuno-compromised. If anything (given my allergy history) I have too robust of an immune response to everything I will definitely follow back up if this develops into shingles. I would be very shocked if it were shingles. I am wondering if the vaccine did not get my immune system so primed that it's attacking anything remotely foreign (varicella zoster dormant in my trigeminal nerve perhaps?) such that I would have itching and burning pain associated with shingles but no actual outbreak of shingles (let's hope there's no outbreak coming later...). Another tidbit of information that suggests robust immune response is that I took my regular allergy shots on Monday, 22 Mar 2021 and the spots (2 shots) whealed up higher than usual. Those went down by morning of 23 Mar 2021 but the Moderna arm has stayed and the V1 burning/itching sensation continues. I am a psychiatrist, so I know my symptoms are not currently worrisome enough to seek medical care. I will if symptoms worsen.

Contact transmission of vaccinia; secondary transmission from mother to child; This case was obtained from a scientific literature titled "Contact transmission of vaccinia to an infant diagnosed by viral culture and metagenomic sequencing", on date 11MAR2021.   Literature citation: Contact transmission of vaccinia to an infant diagnosed by viral culture and metagenomic sequencing. Open Forum Infect Dis. 2020.   A 10-month-old female infant who had "contact transmission of vaccinia; sores on the baby's hands and mouth were a result of autoinoculation" (PT: Vaccinia virus infection) following Vaccinia transmission was suspected with ACAM2000 (smallpox vaccine, live). It was reported that an "occult transmission from a recent vaccine to the mother, and then from mother to child, to be the most likely etiology of the child's skin lesions in this case" (PT: Secondary transmission).    Case report: It was reported that she was presented to a hospital for evaluation of fever and new skin lesions. On exam, the diaper area had 10 circular to irregularly shaped ulcers, 1-2.5 cm in size, with undermined borders, all painful to touch. The parents reported "blisters" that developed 4-5 days prior and ulcerated in the following days. Scattered red macules were noted in perioral and acral locations.   The patient had received no medical care before this illness, and she was behind in her vaccines, not travel and no animal exposure or recent changes in topical hygiene products. The patient improved with supportive care. Vaccinia immune globulin and antivirals with anti-vaccinia activity were considered for treatment of the skin lesions but ultimately were not administered.   The patient's mother had a history of moderate to severe atopic dermatitis and reported a recent illness and flare of her skin disease. On exam, she had numerous circular collarettes of scale over her forearms and arms from a vesicular eruption that began the week prior but was resolving without intervention. The patient's father, an active-duty military member, had a 1-cm vesicular, crusted plaque above his right upper lip, which he attributed to a cold sore. Neither parent, nor other close contacts, had received recent live-virus vaccinations.    At the time of this report, the child's parents had not undergone testing for vaccinia exposure, and a follow-up epidemiologic investigation failed to identify another potential source of exposure. As neither parent had been recently vaccinated, the author considered occult transmission from a recent vaccinee to the mother, and then from mother to child, to be the most likely etiology of the child's skin lesions in this case. Given the distribution of the child's lesions, it was suspected that transmission occurred during diaper care and that the sores on the baby's hands and mouth were a result of autoinoculation.   The author commented that ACAM2000 contains replication-competent virus that can be shed from the intradermal vaccination site for up to 3 weeks, and this vaccine was in use during the time this patient developed infection. As many military members in the father's workplace receive ACAM2000 vaccine, it was theoretically possible that contact transmission resulted in unrecognized secondary vaccinia infection in the father, with or without tertiary infection in the mother, subsequently followed by infection in this infant. Secondary transmission to the child through fomites in the household is also possible, although less likely based on the location of the lesions and given a lack of identifiable family contact with known recent vaccinees.   Based on the available information in the article, 3 individual case safety reports 21000032LT (infant) 21000033LT (mother) and 21000034LT (father) were created and cross linked in the database.  Company Comment: The company agrees with the author that there was a secondary and tertiary transmission from the mother to the baby. ACAM2000 is a live virus vaccine and has a potential to cause vaccinia infection to household members and close contacts by accidental (contact) inoculation, and the causality of vaccinia virus infection and secondary transmission is assessed as possible. The case does not meet the seriousness criteria but will be submitted to the FDA as required.; Sender's Comments: The company agrees with the author that there was a secondary and tertiary transmission from the mother to the baby. ACAM2000 is a live virus vaccine and has a potential to cause vaccinia infection to household members and close contacts by accidental (contact) inoculation, and the causality of vaccinia virus infection and secondary transmission is assessed as possible. The case does not meet the seriousness criteria but will be submitted to the FDA as required.

Sequencing data analyzed with the v2 Explify Platform identified vaccinia virus.; Test Name: Rubeola virus; Result Unstructured Data: Cells displaying CPE tested negative for rubeola virus antigens; Test Name: Electron microscopy; Result Unstructured Data: The images were consistent with a poxvirus infection, as evidenced by the presence of a large (approx. 350 x 270 nm) brick-shaped virion.; Test Name: Physical examination; Result Unstructured Data: The diaper area had 10 circular to irregularly shaped ulcers, 1-2.5 cm in size, with undermined borders, all painful to touch.; Test Name: Varicella-zoster virus test; Result Unstructured Data: Cells displaying CPE tested negative for varicella-zoster virus; Test Name: Viral culture; Result Unstructured Data: CPE resembling that produced by herpes simplex virus (HSV) was observed in the pRhMK and MRC-5 monolayers on day 4 of incubation.; Test Name: Viral culture; Result Unstructured Data: CPE was again observed only in the pRhMK and MRC-5 vials on day 4 postfiltration.; Test Name: Viral culture; Result Unstructured Data: Testing of MRC-5 and pRhMK displaying CPE for enterovirus antigens (on day 4 and day 5, respectively) using commercially available DFA reagent was negative.; Test Name: Viral culture; Result Unstructured Data: Two days later, repeat staining for enterovirus, HSV-1, and HSV-2 using different commercially available DFA kits to rule out potential false-negative results was also negative.

Products known to have been used by the patient, within two weeks prior to the event, included atorvastatin, bupropion hydrochloride, cetirizine hydrochloride, anxiety medicines, clonazepam, metformin,  metoprolol, and trazodone.  On 01 Mar 2021, the patient received the first dose of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: unknown) and 45 minutes later was extremely dizzy. At home one hour later she started to vomit for one hour constantly, became completely unconscious, didn't remember anything, and was really scared. The last thing she remembered was telling her husband: you need to call somebody because she felt like she was going to die. The patient was taken by ambulance to the hospital and while in the ambulance, the patient was administered medicines for nausea and blood pressure. The blood pressure measurement taken in the ambulance was 215 over 156.  The patient didn't know her address or anything else.  She was released to go home after a few hours, but still felt so sick.  On Sunday night (07-Mar-2021), the patient threw up again.  On an unspecified date, she had a headache like someone was putting pressure on her brain; she also had a fast heartbeat.  Since the vaccine, the patient reported feeling really nauseous and remembering nothing about it.  She is still weak. Treatment information included ondansetron medicine for nausea.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown.   At the time of reporting, the outcome of the event, weak, was considered not recovered/not resolved. On 27 Feb 2021, prior to the onset of the event, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 013A21A) intramuscularly in the right thigh for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 27 FEB 2021, the patient experienced Raised hive (Urticaria) about the size of a half dollar, after that she "felt off" (fall) had a headache (Headache) and Felt crappy (Malaise), and she had a couple of bad breakthrough bleeding episodes (Hemorrhage) which was assessed as medically significant, and the patient also experienced interrupted Menstrual cycle (Menstrual disorder). On 07 MAR 2021, the patient experienced Turning into a bruise (Contusion) and on 08 MAR 2021 it was weird again (Feeling abnormal).  Laboratory details were not provided.  Treatment medication was provided as Tylenol.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported.   At the time of this report, the outcome of the events Hemorrhage, Menstrual disorder, Contusion, Malaise, Feeling abnormal, Fall, Urticaria and Headache was considered as unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.
CUR_ILL: Migraine (She is on birth control because of migraines.)

The patient's medical history as provided by the reporter included Neuropathy of feet, elevated Cholesterol, Osteoarthritis, Aortic aneurysm. Admitted to hospital on 12 Feb 2021 and  discharged on 13 Feb 2021. She had stress test, echo, CT and x-rays all were normal. She followed up with her PCP on 15 Feb 2021 and was told that she might have starting of something like bronchitis. The events caused hospitalization and was serious.  Treatment included  antibiotics and steroid shot and prescribed inhaler.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown. HISTORY: lyme - not sure if it's chronic but two confirmed acute cases

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient reported to check-out table approximately 13 minutes after receipt of vaccine complaining of feeling "hot and dizzy".  I was called to patient's side to evaluate.  A pulse ox was placed and gave a reading of SPO2 100% and HR 80.  Quick history was taken and patient was moved outside due to cooler temperatures.  Patient was able to ambulate under her own power and did not appear ill or have any signs of respiratory distress or AMS.  She did note a sensation of tingling/numbness in her lips after sitting down outside  There were no signs of labial edema or edema of the airway.  Patient was given cold water and 25mg po Benadryl with improvement in symptoms 25 minutes later.  After her extended observation period patient was released from the vaccine site with strict follow up precautions.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I felt really funny after the vaccine. I picked up my girls and we went to eat. They told me I was very quiet. When we were going home they told me I was swerving, all over the road and they told me to stop, they would drive, I said no, i don't trust anyone with my car. We got home, I remember changing into my nightgown and was texting someone and I suddenly I stopped. After that I was unresponsive. I would not answer anyone, they said I looked pale and stared into the air. They called my children and they came and emergency personnel was called. I was taken to a hospital and they transferred me to another hospital. I stayed there for 3-4 days. After going home it took me some days to be able to walk without assistance. I wanted to say I had covid in May (1st time) and September (2nd time) . I still do not have taste or smell back from the covid. I can only eat 3 or 4 bites and then I am done.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Immediate warm tingling started in my arm and then went through my whole body and left me feeling week. Then my heart started racing (between 90-110 and I tried to stay relaxed and take deep breaths then my mouth got very dry and my tongue felt like it swelled slightly. By then it had been 10 minutes and nothing was getting worse and I had no problems breathing and didn't feel dizzy so I stayed and waited 10 more minutes and nothing changed so I went home. Symptoms continued for another 45 minutes then I had diarrhea and then slowly my heart rate started going back down to normal my tongue went back to normal and I stopped feeling weak. (about 1 1/4 hours after shot).  Its been 2 days and no new problems.  Usually allergic reactions stay in my body much longer and I continue to have symptoms for at least 24 hours so that was odd too.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got the chills, layed down and tried to warm up. My left arm is in pain. fell asleep briefly, woke up to extreme stabbing pains in the right temple of my head. I barely could walk to the bathroom and I layed on the floor because of the pain in my head. I can feel the pulse of my heartbeat in my head. I had intense nausea. I managed to get to bed. I drove to work the next day but my boss sent me home because I was the same. My eyes feel like they are flickering and are in pain. I feel like its a nerve in my eyes that are messing with me and are very painful. I am afraid to take the second shot.
After 8 days, large lump at injection site. Warm to touch. Red rash.

Six hours after the shot at 6 PM in the evening, I went from a resting heart rate of 65 when it jumped to 100, then 105 and 108.  I have not suffered a tachycardia event for over two years. I worked hard through diet and exercise to change my heart palpitations. But this event lasted for about 30 minutes give or take and we treated at home via breathing meditation exercises. During and afterwards, I experienced Sharp pain and burning underneath the breast bone by the heart. Gerd-type symptoms in the lower esophagus also plagued me. At 1 AM I was awoken to an extreme nausea sensation. As of the next day, my heart feels better but my stomach feels off. I am able to hold foods down.
HISTORY: Neutropenia, reynauds (autoimmune), Epstein Barr (past autoimmune), heart valve regurgitation (floppy valve), DVT (past), MTHFR (clotting risk)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Had typical arm pain after an injection that was to be expected. Rates 3/10 on pain scale. Noticeable decrease in strength in arm where vaccine was administered as well.  I chose the dominant arm, as I am aware that the more the movement of the muscle the less likely the vaccine would pool in the muscle. I am an RN, I received vaccines through out my life time and I have never had a similar outcome. I typically do quite well with vaccinations. I had no other symptoms or reactions to either doses. Arm pain was significant with the first dose and did resolve fully. The arm pain with the second dose was increased in severity and then did decrease however it has not resolved. Concerned due to length of time that has passed.
